Here is the commit message:
Add processExternalEntities support to OXM

Update OXM AbstractMarshaller to support processing of external
XML entities. By default external entities will not be processed.

Issue: SPR-11376

Here is the root cause:
The bug was caused by the lack of support for processing external XML entities in the OXM (Object-XML Mapping) framework, which could lead to XML External Entity (XXE) vulnerabilities. By default, external entities were not processed, but the absence of a configurable option to enable or disable this feature left the system vulnerable to potential attacks when handling XML data. The modifications introduced a mechanism to control this behavior, allowing developers to specify whether external entities should be processed or not.

